  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Correct.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] sorry, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Continuous, but the frequency changed radically at the outbreak of war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, between-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] excuse me-- between getting to Bradford in March '39 and the outbreak of war in September '39, it was very frequent correspondence.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Between September '39 and '42, it was-- the only communications that were allowed in wartime were Red Cross messages, which were messages not exceeding-- personal messages not exceeding 25 words, which were sent by the sender to the Red Cross in Switzerland, and passed by the-- by the Swiss Red Cross to the other-- to the recipient.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then the answer came back the same way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It took a long time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so, therefore, it was limited already by, by that fact-- the frequency was limited by that fact; and, of course, also by the need to be extremely circumspect; and worst of all, to be-- to say everything [LAUGHS] in 25 words.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I have kept a few of those-- of those messages to this day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's amazing what one can pack into 25 words.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- so the, the, the nature and frequency of the communications changed very radically at the outbreak of war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When was the last communication you had with, with your parents and with your sister?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In '42-- it would be in late '42, early '43.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The reason being that my sister was arrested in July of '43 and deported to the east to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] this was a week after her [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] birthday.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Which birthday-- in '43, 21st birthday.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
